Music is displaying incorrect playback times for most MP3 songs. Example screenshots:

![Screenshot_from_2019-12-04_09-20-16](/uploads/9b74e5c90c5c6da132e5e905e6055fb1/Screenshot_from_2019-12-04_09-20-16.png)

Music says the album length is 89 minutes, but it is actually 76 minutes [according to Wikipedia](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Octavarium). For longer songs, it displays a duration that is too long. Music says the first song is 9:19, but it's actually 8:07 according to nautilus (or 8:08 according to totem, which rounds differently). It says the last song is 34:47, but nautilus correctly says 23:58. Note the screenshot shows the trackbar slider almost to the very end of the song, but only at 23:14, nowhere near the reported ending time of 34:47.

With other songs, Music displays a duration that is too short. At the end of these songs, it is possible to see the current position in the song is after the end of the song. For example, below we see Music paused at 2:33 in a song that is supposedly only 2:28 long. (No judging my musical preferences!)

![Screenshot_from_2019-11-30_13-03-40](/uploads/5fba483f6b0d39b635bbd7e8fc8d645d/Screenshot_from_2019-11-30_13-03-40.png)

The track bar is correct, and the current position in the song is correct. But the duration labels, the end times, are all wrong. I can provide mp3s to reproduce out-of-band, upon request.

I've tracked down the problem as far as the mp3_parse_header() function in tracker-extract-mp3.c. Here the wrong length gets computed in the first condition branch:

```
	if ((!vbr_flag && frames > VBR_THRESHOLD) || (frames > MAX_FRAMES_SCAN)) {
		/* If not all frames scanned
		 * Note that bitrate is always > 0, checked before */
		length = (filedata->size - filedata->id3v2_size) / (avg_bps ? avg_bps : bitrate) / 125;
	} else {
		/* Note that sample_rate is always > 0, checked before */
		length = spfp8 * 8 * frames / sample_rate;
	}
```

In the Road to Fallarbor Town mp3, the values there are:

```
length=148 <- (filedata->size=4785989 - filedata->id3v2_size=154634) / avg_bps=249 / 125
```

which results in a length that is five seconds too short. The computed duration is 148 but the correct answer is 153. I don't know which part of this computation is wrong, though.

This is occurring with tracker-miners-2.3.0-1.fc31, but I also built git master locally to manually test tracker-extract and it occurs the same there. The relevant code has not changed in the past decade, which is very strange because I'm almost certain this bug is a recent regression within the past few months.

